abstract: Kansas Supreme Court unanimously strikes down 2014 law stripping it of power to appoint chief judges for trial courts in state’s 31 judicial districts, setting up fight with lawmakers who threatened to defund judiciary if law were overturned.
lead_paragraph: The State Supreme Court on Wednesday unanimously struck down a law meant to reduce its administrative influence over lower courts.

headline.main: Kansas: High Court Strikes Law Cutting Its Power
